    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-01-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="30"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A14/43</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary General of the League of Nations</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Drummond</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-01-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 8, 1925</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received January 27.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">C. L. 192.1924. IX</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In pursuance of my letter of December 9th,
                        1924,<note n="39" xml:id="d30fn1">Not printed.</note> I have the honour to
                    inform you that, at its meeting held in Rome on December <pb facs="0153" n="27"
                        xml:id="pg_27"/> 9th, 1924, the Council of the League of Nations decided
                    that the International Conference to examine the draft Convention for the
                    control of the international traffic in arms, munitions and implements of war,
                    prepared by the Temporary Mixed Commission for the reduction of armaments,<note
                        n="40" xml:id="d30fn2">For draft convention, see <ref
                            target="frus1924v01#pg_56">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1924, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 56</ref>; also League of Nations, <hi
                            rend="italic">Report of the Temporary Mixed Commission for the Reduction
                            of Armaments</hi> (A. 16. 1924. IX, annex IV).</note> and to conclude a
                    Convention on this matter, will meet at the Secretariat of the League of Nations
                    in Geneva on Monday, May 4th, 1925 at 4 p.m.</p>
                <p>The Governments of the following countries have already signified their
                    willingness to be present at this Conference: <list>
                        <item>Austria</item>
                        <item>Belgium</item>
                        <item>Brazil</item>
                        <item>Bulgaria</item>
                        <item>China</item>
                        <item>Czechoslovakia</item>
                        <item>Denmark</item>
                        <item>Esthonia</item>
                        <item>Finland</item>
                        <item>France</item>
                        <item>Germany</item>
                        <item>Great Britain</item>
                        <item>Greece</item>
                        <item>Hungary</item>
                        <item>India</item>
                        <item>Italy</item>
                        <item>Japan<note n="*" xml:id="d30fn3">The participation of Japan is
                                conditional upon the representation at the Conference of the States
                                mentioned in Article 32 of the draft Convention. These States are
                                Belgium, United States of America, France, Great Britain, Italy,
                                Japan and Russia. [Footnote in the original.]</note>
                        </item>
                        <item>Kingdom of the Serbs, Croats &amp; Slovenes</item>
                        <item>Latvia</item>
                        <item>Netherlands</item>
                        <item>Persia</item>
                        <item>Poland</item>
                        <item>Spain</item>
                        <item>Sweden</item>
                        <item>Switzerland</item>
                        <item>United States of America</item>
                        <item>Uruguay.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>[Signature illegible]<lb/>[For the] Secretary-General</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
